verses.text_plain: And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,
verses.verse_html: 1And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,

verses.text_plain: Speak unto the children of Israel, and take of every one of them a rod according to the house of their fathers, of all their princes according to the house of their fathers twelve rods: write thou every man’s name upon his rod.
verses.verse_html: 2Speak unto the children of Israel, and take of every one of them a rod according to the house of their fathers, of all their princes according to the house of their fathers twelve rods: write thou every man’s name upon his rod.

tokens.text: of every one of them a rod

verses.text_plain: And thou shalt write Aaron’s name upon the rod of Levi: for one rod shall be for the head of the house of their fathers.
verses.verse_html: 3And thou shalt write Aaron’s name upon the rod of Levi: for one rod shall be for the head of the house of their fathers.

verses.text_plain: And thou shalt lay them up in the tabernacle of the congregation before the testimony, where I will meet with you.
verses.verse_html: 4And thou shalt lay them up in the tabernacle of the congregation before the testimony, where I will meet with you.

tokens.text: And thou shalt lay them up

verses.text_plain: And it shall come to pass, that the man’s rod, whom I shall choose, shall blossom: and I will make to cease from me the murmurings of the children of Israel, whereby they murmur against you.
verses.verse_html: 5And it shall come to pass, that the man’s rod, whom I shall choose, shall blossom: and I will make to cease from me the murmurings of the children of Israel, whereby they murmur against you.

tokens.text: and I will make to cease

verses.text_plain: And Moses spake unto the children of Israel, and every one of their princes gave him a rod apiece, for each prince one, according to their fathers’ houses, even twelve rods: and the rod of Aaron was among their rods.
verses.verse_html:
6And Moses spake unto the children of Israel, and every one of their princes gave him a rod apiece, for each prince one, according to their fathers’ houses, even twelve rods: and the rod of Aaron was among their rods. ▼
▼ a rod…: Heb. a rod for one prince, a rod for one prince

tokens.text: and every one of their princes

footnotes.body_text: ▼ a rod…: Heb. a rod for one prince, a rod for one prince
footnotes.body_html: ▼ a rod…: Heb. a rod for one prince, a rod for one prince

verses.text_plain: And Moses laid up the rods before the Lord in the tabernacle of witness.
verses.verse_html: 7And Moses laid up the rods before the Lord in the tabernacle of witness.

verses.text_plain: And it came to pass, that on the morrow Moses went into the tabernacle of witness; and, behold, the rod of Aaron for the house of Levi was budded, and brought forth buds, and bloomed blossoms, and yielded almonds.
verses.verse_html: 8And it came to pass, that on the morrow Moses went into the tabernacle of witness; and, behold, the rod of Aaron for the house of Levi was budded, and brought forth buds, and bloomed blossoms, and yielded almonds.

tokens.text: And it came to pass, that on the morrow

verses.text_plain: And Moses brought out all the rods from before the Lord unto all the children of Israel: and they looked, and took every man his rod.
verses.verse_html: 9And Moses brought out all the rods from before the Lord unto all the children of Israel: and they looked, and took every man his rod.

verses.text_plain: And the Lord said unto Moses, Bring Aaron’s rod again before the testimony, to be kept for a token against the rebels; and thou shalt quite take away their murmurings from me, that they die not.
verses.verse_html:
10And the Lord said unto Moses, Bring Aaron’s rod again before the testimony, to be kept for a token against the rebels; and thou shalt quite take away their murmurings from me, that they die not. ▼
▼ rebels: Heb. children of rebellion

tokens.text: and thou shalt quite take away

footnotes.body_html: ▼ rebels: Heb. children of rebellion

verses.text_plain: And Moses did so: as the Lord commanded him, so did he.
verses.verse_html: 11And Moses did so: as the Lord commanded him, so did he.

verses.text_plain: And the children of Israel spake unto Moses, saying, Behold, we die, we perish, we all perish.
verses.verse_html: 12And the children of Israel spake unto Moses, saying, Behold, we die, we perish, we all perish.

verses.text_plain: Whosoever cometh any thing near unto the tabernacle of the Lord shall die: shall we be consumed with dying?
verses.verse_html: 13Whosoever cometh any thing near unto the tabernacle of the Lord shall die: shall we be consumed with dying?
